question_text:
For any positive integer $$m$$, $$n$$ (with $$n \ge m$$), let $$\left( {\matrix{
   n  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) = {}^n{C_m}$$  
Prove that  $$\left( {\matrix{
   n  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) + \left( {\matrix{
   {n - 1}  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) + \left( {\matrix{
   {n - 2}  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) + ........ + \left( {\matrix{
   m  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) = \left( {\matrix{
   {n + 1}  \cr 
   {m + 2}  \cr 

 } } \right)$$ 
Hence or otherwise, prove that $$\left( {\matrix{
   n  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) + 2\left( {\matrix{
   {n - 1}  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) + 3\left( {\matrix{
   {n - 2}  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) + ........ + \left( {n - m + 1} \right)\left( {\matrix{
   m  \cr 
   m  \cr 

 } } \right) = \left( {\matrix{
   {n + 2}  \cr 
   {m + 2}  \cr 

 } } \right).$$.
